What dataset to use
For a search engine over CS research papers, you have two strong options:

Option 1 — CORD-19 (recommended) Available at https://allenai.org/data/cord-19 — it's listed directly in your assignment brief's Appendix B. It contains 500,000+ scholarly articles with structured metadata including titles, abstracts, author keywords, and full body text. It's widely cited in academic literature, which means you can find IEEE/ACM papers that reference it — satisfying the "dataset referenced by someone else" requirement your notes highlight in capitals.

Option 2 — arXiv CS papers via Kaggle Search Kaggle for "arxiv dataset" — there's a well-known snapshot with ~2 million papers. It includes title, abstract, authors, categories, and doi. The CS subset alone gives you tens of thousands of papers. Kaggle datasets are citable and used extensively in published work.

What fields to extract
Not all columns are useful. Per your notes: "use only the necessary columns". The fields you need are:

Field	Why you need it
title	High-weight source — nouns in titles are very indicative
abstract	Primary text for TF-IDF indexing
