Good — app.py looks correct now. Let me explain what's happening with clicks and then verify the flow is working end to end.

How clicks are supposed to work:

You search for something — results appear
You click a title or "Open paper" — that fires a POST to /click which increments the count in memory AND saves to click_store.pkl
You search the same query again — the blended score for that document goes up and it ranks higher
The click score pills on the results update to reflect it
The key point is that clicks only affect the next search, not the current one. The current results don't re-render automatically — you have to search again to see the re-ranking. This is by design and matches how real search engines work.

